<title>Providing the facts to help Europe achieve 55%</title>
<description><![CDATA[
	<img src="https://www.esa.int/var/esa/storage/images/esa_multimedia/images/2020/07/industrial_emissions_of_carbon_dioxide_fuel_our_warming_climate/22159848-1-eng-GB/Industrial_emissions_of_carbon_dioxide_fuel_our_warming_climate_card_full.jpg" alt="Industrial emissions of carbon dioxide fuel our warming climate">
	<p>Today, at her State of the Union address before the European Parliament, Ursula von der Leyen, President of the European Commission, proposed a new target of a 55% cut in greenhouse gas emissions by 2030, compared to 1990 levels. The current target is a 40% reduction. With such ambitious goals ahead for Europe, understanding how greenhouse gases end up in the atmosphere and the intricacies of the carbon cycle is essential – something that satellites observing Earth can help provide.</p>
]]></description>
<link><![CDATA[https://www.esa.int/Applications/Observing_the_Earth/Space_for_our_climate/Providing_the_facts_to_help_Europe_achieve_55]]></link>

